President Trump welcomed recipients of the Congressional Medal of Honor to the White House for a reception. He expressed his admiration and gratitude for their bravery and sacrifice, calling them the strongest, bravest, and finest among us. The President also provided an update on preparations for incoming hurricanes and urged residents in the path of the storms to comply with evacuation orders. He thanked members of his Cabinet and military leaders in attendance, and acknowledged the presence of three recipients of the Medal of Honor whom he personally presented the award to. The President praised the courage and heroism of all the recipients, and emphasized the importance of supporting and honoring veterans. He concluded by pledging his unwavering support for the military and veterans, and defending the country and its values.